    <fr:title text="Prime spectra of Boolean algebras">Prime spectra of Boolean algebras</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  Let us consider a Boolean algebra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} B]]></fr:tex> is the Stone space associated to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>. In particular, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {B}[x]]]></fr:tex> is the free Boolean algebra generated by one element, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\mathbb {B}[x] \cong  2]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2]]></fr:tex> is the discrete set.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
